{"lemma":"سَحَرَ","slug":"سَحَرَ","root":"س.ح.ر","root_slug":"س-ح-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ح-ر","pos":"V","pos_camel":"verb","paradigm":[{"role":"past_2ms","form":"سَحَرْتَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2fs","form":"سَحَرْتِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_2md","form":"سَحَرْتُما","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_2mp","form":"سَحَرْتُم","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_2fp","form":"سَحَرْتُنَّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3ms","form":"سَحَرَ","in_corpus":true,"count":2,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3fs","form":"سَحَرَت","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"past_3md","form":"سَحَرا","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3fd","form":"سَحَرَتا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"past_3mp","form":"سَحَرُوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_3fp","form":"سَحَرْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2ms","form":"تَسْحَر","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَسْحَرِينَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2fs","form":"تَسْحَرِي","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَسْحَرا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2md","form":"تَسْحَرانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَسْحَرُوا","in_corpus":true,"count":1,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2mp","form":"تَسْحَرُونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_2fp","form":"تَسْحَرْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"2","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3ms","form":"يَسْحَر","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3fs","form":"تَسْحَر","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"s"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَسْحَرا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3md","form":"يَسْحَرانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَسْحَرا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3fd","form":"تَسْحَرانِ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"d"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَسْحَرُوا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3mp","form":"يَسْحَرُونَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_3fp","form":"يَسْحَرْنَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"3","gen":"f","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"سَحَرْنا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"سَحَرْتُ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَسْحَر","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَسْحَر","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"}],"frequency_in_corpus":4,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَحَر","root":"سحر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":14},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19071","n19075","n19076","n19077","n19078","n19079","n19080"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dawn","tags":["archaic","literary"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"predawn"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"foredawn, especially the last part of the night before daybreak"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to eat before fasting at predawn or foredawn, especially in the last part of the night before daybreak"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lung"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to charm, to enchant, to fascinate, to spellbind, to bewitch, to ensorcel, to curse, to jinx"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hurt one's heart, to restrict one's chest or breathing"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to conjure"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bewitch, to charm"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَحَرَ (saḥara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"charming, enchantment, fascination, spellbinding"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"witchcraft, sorcery, magic, wizardry"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"conjuring, bewitching"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"charm, curse, jinx"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *šaḥ(a)r- (“dawn, morning”). Cognate with Akkadian 𒀉𒄘𒍣𒂵 (šērum), Hebrew שַׁחַר (šáḥar, “dawn”) and Ugaritic 𐎌𐎈𐎗 (šḥr, “dawn; tomorrow, the future”); see Canaanite deity Shahar."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19071","headword_ar":"سحّر","root":"sHr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasoHiyrN","text_ar":"تَسْحِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, in four places. ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fed"},{"kind":"text","text":"another, or others,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the food,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meal, called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHuwr","text_ar":"سَحُور"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, Mgh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~arahumo","text_ar":"سَحَّرَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he gave to them the meal so called."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Mgh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n19075","headword_ar":"سَحْرٌ","root":"sHr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHarN","text_ar":"سَحَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) sometimes thus because of the faucial letter, (S,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHorN","text_ar":"سُحْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and, accord. to El-Khafájee, in the 'Ináyeh, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siHorN","text_ar":"سِحْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this is not mentioned by any other, and therefore requires confirmation, (TA,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lungs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lights:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what adheres to the gullet and the windpipe, of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the contents of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the upper part of the belly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"all that hangs to the gullet, consisting of the heart and liver and lungs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the exterior of the body corresponding to the place of the lungs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA: *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHorN","text_ar":"سَحْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liver; and"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"core,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inner part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAd","text_ar":"سَوَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sides,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regions, of the heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHorN","text_ar":"سُحْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ElJarmee, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHorapN","text_ar":"سُحْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) the pl. (of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHorN","text_ar":"سَحْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, Msb) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHuwrN","text_ar":"سُحُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and (of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHorN","text_ar":"سُحْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, Msb, and of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHarN","text_ar":"سَحَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoHaArN","text_ar":"اَسْحَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ainotafaxa saHoruhu","text_ar":"اِنْتَفَخَ سَحْرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ainotafaxato","text_ar":"اِنْتَفَخَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAHiruhu","text_ar":"مَسَاحِرُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His lungs became inflated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swollen, by reason of timidity and cowardice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) said of a coward: (S:) and of one who has exceeded his due bounds: Lth says that, when repletion arises in a man, one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Antfx sHrh","text_ar":"انتفخ سحره"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that the meaning is, [as given also in the K,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he exceeded his due bounds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Az says that this is a mistake, and that this phrase is only said of a coward, whose inside is filled with fear, and whose lungs are inflated, or swollen, so that the heart is raised to the gullet: and of the same kind is the phrase in the Kur [xxxiii. 10]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabalagati Alquluwbu AlHanaAjira","text_ar":"وَبَلَغَتِ القُلُوبُ الحَنَاجِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuqaT~aEapu","text_ar":"المُقَطَّعَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^asoHaAri","text_ar":"الاَسْحَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uHuwri","text_ar":"السُّحُورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She that has her lungs burst asunder"},{"kind":"text","text":"], an appellation given to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aronab","text_ar":"اَرْنَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hare,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female hare"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, K,) or to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the swift"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Arnb","text_ar":"ارنب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qTE","text_ar":"قطع"},{"kind":"text","text":",) by way of good omen, meaning that her lungs will burst asunder; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuqaT~aEapu Aln~iyaATi","text_ar":"المُقَطَّعَةُ النِّيَاطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and some (of those of later times, S) say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuqaT~iEapu","text_ar":"المُقَطِّعَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"T","text_ar":"ط"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) as though, by her speed and vehemence of running, she would burst asunder her lungs; (S;) or because she bursts the lungs of the dogs by the vehemence of her running, and the lungs of him who purses her. (ISh, Sgh.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinoqaTaEa minohu saHoriY","text_ar":"اِنْقَطَعَ مِنْهُ سَحْرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I despaired of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA minohu gayoru Sariymi saHorK","text_ar":"اَنَا مِنْهُ غَيْرُ صَرِيمِ سَحْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am not in despair of him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, B.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sariymu saHorK","text_ar":"صَرِيمُ سَحْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also expl. as signifying (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having his hope cut off:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (tropical:)  anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"despaired of."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Surima saHoruhu","text_ar":"صُرِمَ سَحْرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His hope was cut off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scar of a gall on the back of a camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it has healed, and the place thereof has become white."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"highest, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a valley. (TA.)       -A4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~aArapN","text_ar":"سَحَّارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A5-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHarN","text_ar":"سَحَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","A"]},{"entry_id":"n19076","headword_ar":"سُحْرٌ","root":"sHr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n19077","headword_ar":"سِحْرٌ","root":"sHr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHorN","text_ar":"سَحْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence.       -A2-  [Also] an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHarahu","text_ar":"سَحَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turning"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its proper manner of being to another manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA: [accord. to the T, this seems to be proper; but accord. to the A, tropical:]) and hence, (T, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enchantment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fascination:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, * S, * MA, KL, PS:) for when. the enchanter ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aAHiru","text_ar":"السَّاحِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") makes what is false to appear in the form of truth, and causes a thing to be imagined different from what it really is, it is as though he turned it from its proper manner of being: (T, TA:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"producing what is false in the form of truth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, Msb:) or, in the common conventional language of the law,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any event of which the cause is hidden, and which is imagined to be different from what it really is:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"embellishment by falsification, and deceit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fakhred-Deen, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a performance in which one allies himself to the devil, and which is effected by his aid:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axo*apN","text_ar":"اَخْذَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of enchantment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fascination, which captivates the eye and the like, and by which enchantresses withhold their husbands from other women"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything of which the way of proceeding"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"operation"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^oxa*uhu","text_ar":"مَاْخَذُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is subtile:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) accord. to Ibn-Abee-'Áïsheh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siHor","text_ar":"سِحْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is thus called by the Arabs because it changes health, or soundness, to disease: (Sh:) [and in like manner it is said to change hatred to love: (see 1:)] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoHaArN","text_ar":"اَسْحَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHuwrN","text_ar":"سُحُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Skilful eloquence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or used absolutely, it is applied to that for which the agent is blamed: and when restricted, to that which is praiseworthy. (Msb.) Thus it is in the saying of Mohammad,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a mina AlbayaAni lasiHorFA","text_ar":"اـِنَّ مِنَ البَيَانِ لَسِحْرًا"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1317},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily there is a kind of eloquence that is enchantment"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: because the speaker propounds an obscure matter, and discloses its true meaning by the beauty of his eloquence, inclining the hearts [of his hearers] in like manner as they are inclined by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siHor","text_ar":"سِحْر"},{"kind":"text","text":": or because there is in eloquence a novelty and strangeness of composition which attracts the hearer and brings him to such a pass as almost diverts him from other things; therefore it is likened to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siHor","text_ar":"سِحْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly so called: and it is said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~iHoru AlHalaAlu","text_ar":"السِّحْرُ الحَلَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lawful enchantment"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) The saying of Mohammad mentioned above was uttered on the following occasion: Keys Ibn-'Ásim El-Minkaree and EzZibrikán Ibn-Bedr and 'Amr Ibn-El-Ahtam came to the Prophet, who asked 'Amr respecting EzZibrikán; whereupon he spoke well of him: but Ez-Zibrikán was not content with this, and said, “ By God, O apostle of God, he knows that I am more excellent than he has said; but he envies the place that I have in thine estimation: ” and thereupon 'Amr spoke ill of him; and then said, “ By God, I did not lie of him in the first saying nor in the other; but he pleased me, and I spoke as pleased; then he angered me, and I spoke as angered: ” then Mohammad uttered the above-mentioned words. (TA.) Their meaning is, but God knows best, he praises the man, speaking truth respecting him, so as to turn the hearts of the hearers to him, (K,) or to what he says; (TA;) and he dispraises him, speaking truth respecting him, so as to turn their hearts also to him, (K,) or to what he says after. (TA.) A' Obeyd says nearly the same. Or, as some say, the meaning is, that there is an eloquence that is sinful like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siHor","text_ar":"سِحْر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Skill; science:"},{"kind":"text","text":"Mohammad said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano taEal~ama baAbFA mina Aln~ujuwmi faqado","text_ar":"مَنْ تَعَلَّمَ بَابًا مِنَ النُّجُومِ فَقَدْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEal~ama baAbFA mina Als~iHori","text_ar":"تَعَلَّمَ بَابًا مِنَ السِّحْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who learneth a process of the science of the stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"astrology"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"astronomy) learneth a process of enchantment"},{"kind":"text","text":"], which may mean that the science of the stars is forbidden to be learned, like the science of enchantment, and that the learning of it is an act of infidelity: or it may mean that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"science;"},{"kind":"text","text":"referring to what is acquired thereof by way of calculation; as the knowledge of eclipses of the sun or moon, and the like. (ISd, TA.) ―         -b4-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Food; aliment; nutriment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because its effect is subtile. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gayovN *uw siHorK","text_ar":"غَيْثٌ ذُو سِحْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Superabundant rain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","TA","IF","Msb","S","K","Sh"]},{"entry_id":"n19078","headword_ar":"سَحَرٌ","root":"sHr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHorN","text_ar":"سَحْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  Also, (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHorN","text_ar":"سَحْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHurN","text_ar":"سُحُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHariY~N","text_ar":"سَحَرِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHariy~apN","text_ar":"سَحَرِيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time a little before daybreak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before daybreak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last part of the night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last sixth of the night:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHarN","text_ar":"سَحَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHorN","text_ar":"سَحْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHurN","text_ar":"سُحُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoHaArN","text_ar":"اَسْحَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, K, TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHar","text_ar":"سَحَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is thus met. called because it is the time of the departure of the night and the coming of the day; so that it is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutanaf~as","text_ar":"مُتَنَفَّس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit. the “ time of the breathing, ” by which is meant the “ shining forth, ”] of the dawn: (A:) there are two times of which each is thus called; one, which is [specially] called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aHaru AlA^aEolaY","text_ar":"السَّحَرُ الاَعْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the earlier"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHar","text_ar":"سَحَر"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (A, Mgh,) is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before daybreak;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little before daybreak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and the other,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at daybreak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh:) like as one says “ the false dawn ” and “ the true: ” (A:) the earlier"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHar","text_ar":"سَحَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHorapN","text_ar":"سُحْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHorap","text_ar":"سُحْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"same as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHar","text_ar":"سَحَر"},{"kind":"text","text":": or it is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"last third of the night, to daybreak."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Using"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHar","text_ar":"سَحَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"indeterminately, you make it perfectly decl., and say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotuhu bisaHarK","text_ar":"اَتَيْتُهُ بِسَحَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to him a little before daybreak"},{"kind":"text","text":"], agreeably with the phrase in the Kur liv. 34; (S;) and in like manner, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bisuHorapK","text_ar":"بِسُحْرَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the earlier"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHar","text_ar":"سَحَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) you also say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHarFA","text_ar":"سَحَرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHorapF","text_ar":"سُحْرَةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHarFA mina AlA^asoHaAri","text_ar":"سَحَرًا مِنَ الاَسْحَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA zaAla","text_ar":"مَا زَالَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinodanaA muno*u Als~aHari","text_ar":"عِنْدَنَا مُنْذُ السَّحَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ceased not to be with us,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at our abode, from a little before daybreak"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu biAls~aHari AlA^aEolaY","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ بِالسَّحَرِ الاَعْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA^aEolaY saHarayoni","text_ar":"بِاَعْلَى سَحَرَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA^aEolaY Als~aHarayoni","text_ar":"بِاَعْلَى السَّحَرَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^aEolaY Als~aHarayoni","text_ar":"فِى اَعْلَى السَّحَرَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I met him in the earlier"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHar","text_ar":"سَحَر"},{"kind":"text","text":";] but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA^aEolaY saHarK","text_ar":"بِاَعْلَى سَحَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a phrase used by El-'Ajjáj, is erroneous: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi All~ayolapi","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ اللَّيْلَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu saHariY~a","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ سَحَرِىَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHariy~atahaA","text_ar":"سَحَرِيَّتَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I met him in the time a little before daybreak of this"},{"kind":"text","text":"last"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"night"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) When, by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHar","text_ar":"سَحَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, you mean the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHar","text_ar":"سَحَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the night immediately preceding, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu saHara yaA h`*aA","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ سَحَرَ يَا هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I met him a little before daybreak this last night, O thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"man], (S, K,) making it imperfectly decl. because it is altered from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aHara","text_ar":"السَّحَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or because it is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAls~aHari","text_ar":"بِالسَّحَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and it is thus determinate by itself, (S, K,) without its being prefixed to another noun and without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and in the same sense you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bisaHara","text_ar":"بِسَحَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siro EalaY farasika saHara yaA fataY","text_ar":"سِرْ عَلَى فَرَسِكَ سَحَرَ يَا فَتَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Go thou on thy horse a little before daybreak this night, O youth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the TA; but in two copies of the S, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siro","text_ar":"سِرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"I find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyra","text_ar":"سِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: you do not make it to terminate with damm, [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabolu","text_ar":"قَبْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEodu","text_ar":"بَعْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] because it is an adv. n. which, in a place where it is fitting to be such, may not be used otherwise than as such: (S:) and [in like manner] you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu suHorapa","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ سُحْرَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA h`*aA","text_ar":"يَا هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I met him in the earlier"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHar","text_ar":"سَحَر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of this last night, O thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"man]. (TA.) If you make"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHar","text_ar":"سَحَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"the proper name of a man, it is perfectly decl.: and so is the dim.; for it is not of the measure of a noun made to deviate from its original from, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uxaru","text_ar":"اُخَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siro EalaY farasika suHayorFA","text_ar":"سِرْ عَلَى فَرَسِكَ سُحَيْرًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Go thou on thy horse a very little before daybreak:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the TA; but here again, in two copies of the S, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siro","text_ar":"سِرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"I find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyra","text_ar":"سِيرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: you do not make it to terminate with damm, [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabolu","text_ar":"قَبْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,] because its being made of the dim. form does not bring it into the class of adv. ns. which may also be used as nouns absolutely, though it does bring it into the class of nouns which are perfectly declinable. (S, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHarN","text_ar":"سَحَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whiteness overspreading blackness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHarN","text_ar":"صَحَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; except that the former is mostly used in relation to the time so called, of daybreak; and the latter, in relation to colours, as when one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimaArN A^aSoHaru","text_ar":"حِمَارٌ اَصْحَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suHorapN","text_ar":"سُحْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuHorapN","text_ar":"صُحْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, K) of a desert, (T,) and of the earth or a land, (A,) or of anything: (K:) from the time of night so called: (A:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoHaArN","text_ar":"اَسْحَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, A, K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","K","S","Lth","Mgh","A","T"]},{"entry_id":"n19079","headword_ar":"سَحِرٌ","root":"sHr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHiyrN","text_ar":"سَحِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n19080","headword_ar":"سُحُرٌ","root":"sHr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHarN","text_ar":"سَحَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence, in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}